 There are regular Android APIs that are very useful in space travel, 

00:01:19.689 --> 00:01:24.390
 Especially the Text-to-Speech API. In space, you will sometimes be unable to look at the screen, 

00:01:24.390 --> 00:01:29.210
 Therefore, the "Read it to me" feature is very useful. The astronauts can then 

00:01:29.210 --> 00:01:33.170
 Listen to an article read through the helmet while they are on the moon, for example. 

00:01:33.170 --> 00:01:37.249
 The test is really important because we need to identify the appropriate features and inappropriate features in space. 

